cat << EOF
ddcutil is a Linux program for querying and changing monitor settings, such as brightness and color levels.

Most monitors, other than laptop displays, have a Virtual Control Panel (VCP), which implements
features defined in the Monitor Control Command Set (MCCS).
Typically, ddcutil communicates with the monitor's VCP over an I2C bus,
as per the Display Data Channel/Command Interface Standard (DDC/CI).
EOF
